.TH "xvip_clr_or_set" 9 "xvip_clr_or_set" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xvip_clr_or_set \- Clear or set the register with a bitmask
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xvip_clr_or_set
.BI "(struct xvip_device *xvip "  ","
.BI "u32 addr "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ","
.BI "bool set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xvip" 12
Xilinx Video IP device
.IP "addr" 12
address of register
.IP "mask" 12
bitmask to be set or cleared
.IP "set" 12
boolean flag indicating whether to set or clear
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Clear or set the register at address \fIaddr\fP with a bitmask \fImask\fP depending on
the boolean flag \fIset\fP. When the flag \fIset\fP is true, the bitmask is set in
the register, otherwise the bitmask is cleared from the register
when the flag \fIset\fP is false.

Fox example, this function can be used to set a control with a boolean value
requested by users. If the caller knows whether to set or clear in the first
place, the caller should call \fBxvip_clr\fP or \fBxvip_set\fP directly instead of
using this function.
